			<h4><a id="comment_link_45324161" name="comment_link_45324161" href="//politics.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=4407723&amp;cid=45324161" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(45324161)" >Re:</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_45324161" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 45324161); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>3</a>, Informative)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span>Anonymous Coward</span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_45324161"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45324161"><p>Whatever you think of what Snowden did, the simple fact is that he is <b>not a traitor</b>.  The US Constitution has a very clear definition of treason, specifically, aiding or giving comfort to an enemy <i>at a time of war declared by Congress</i>.  Congress hasn't declared war since 1942.</p></div>
	</div>

